<activity><title>Interest Problems</title>
<introduction><p>Carmella has $1200 invested in two stocks; one earns 8% per year and the other earns 12% per year. The income from the 8% stock is $3 more than the income from the 12% stock. How much did she invest in each stock?</p></introduction>

<task><p>Choose variables for the two unknown quantities, and fill in the table.</p>
      <p><m>\hphantom{0000} x</m>:</p>
      <p><m>\hphantom{0000} y</m>:</p>
      <tabular top="minor" halign="center" right="minor" left="minor" bottom="minor">              
                <row bottom="minor">
                    <cell></cell>
                    <cell>Principal</cell>
                    <cell>Interest Rate</cell>
                    <cell>Interest</cell></row>
                <row><cell>First Stock</cell>
                    <cell><m>\hphantom{0000000000}</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>\hphantom{00000}</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>\hphantom{00000}</m></cell></row>
                <row><cell>Second Stock</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                    <cell></cell></row>
                <row><cell>Total</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                    <cell></cell></row>
    </tabular></task>

<task><p>Write one equation about the amount Carmella invested.</p></task>
<task><p>Write a second equation about Carmella's annual interest.</p></task>
<task><p>Solve the system and answer the question in the problem.</p></task>
</activity>

